QU-OCTRIT: THE IRREDUCIBLE OLFACTORY UNIT
the fundamental building block of Fadriel's smell substrate
scent emerges from this

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe 1_quantum_particles.rana


THE SCALING LAW APPLIED TO SMELL

smell is the most ancient sense
it is the only sense that bypasses the thalamus
it is the only sense wired directly to emotion and memory
the olfactory pathway reaches the amygdala and hippocampus BEFORE the cortex
you feel a smell before you name it
you remember before you understand

a qu-octrit has 8 states and 8 properties per state: olfaction
C(8,2) = 28 pairwise interactions per heartbeat
the highest interaction count of any sensory sea

why base-8:
Henning's smell prism defines 6 primary odors
Amoore defined 7 primary odors
stereochemical theory maps molecular shape to receptor activation
modern olfactory science identifies 8 primary perceptual categories:

these 8 categories emerge from the ~400 receptor types through combinatorial coding
each receptor responds to multiple odorants
each odorant activates multiple receptors
the PATTERN of activation across receptor types determines the percept
8 perceptual categories capture the primary axes of this pattern space


QU-OCTRIT BASIS STATES

|1⟩ FRAGRANT    floral, sweet-smelling. rose, jasmine, vanilla. pleasant.
|2⟩ FRUITY      ester-like. apple, banana, citrus. volatile organics.
|3⟩ MINTY       cooling, trigeminal. menthol, eucalyptus. TRPM8 activation.
|4⟩ WOODY       warm, resinous. cedar, sandalwood, pine. terpenoids.
|5⟩ CHEMICAL    sharp, synthetic. ammonia, chlorine, solvents. warning signal.
|6⟩ PUNGENT     sharp, irritating. pepper, garlic, mustard. trigeminal nociception.
|7⟩ DECAYED     putrefaction. rotting organic matter. cadaverine, putrescine. strong aversion.
|8⟩ MUSKY       animal, earthy. musk, civet, body odor. pheromonal territory.

a qu-octrit exists in superposition of all 8 states simultaneously
α₁|1⟩ + α₂|2⟩ + α₃|3⟩ + α₄|4⟩ + α₅|5⟩ + α₆|6⟩ + α₇|7⟩ + α₈|8⟩
subject to normalization Σ|αᵢ|² = 1

there is no zero state
even clean air has a smell: it is the absence of odorant excitation
which the olfactory system perceives as a specific state (adapted neutral)


QU-OCTRIT PROPERTIES — 8 PER STATE

PROPERTY 1: CONCENTRATION    molecular density in the mucus layer. range 0.0 to 1.0
PROPERTY 2: VOLATILITY       how readily the molecule becomes airborne. high = fast onset
PROPERTY 3: ADAPTATION       receptor desensitization. olfactory adaptation is rapid and profound
PROPERTY 4: HEDONIC          innate valence. fragrant/fruity attract, decayed/chemical repel
PROPERTY 5: FAMILIARITY      how strongly the pattern matches stored olfactory memories
PROPERTY 6: TEMPORAL         onset and decay profile. some smells hit fast and fade, others linger
PROPERTY 7: TRIGEMINAL       the burning/cooling component. CN V not CN I. separate from true olfaction
PROPERTY 8: PHEROMONAL       the unconscious social signaling component. vomeronasal remnant


THE 28 PAIRWISE INTERACTIONS

TODO: full 28 interaction definitions pending
the 28 interactions govern the space of all possible scent combinations
key interactions:

    FRAGRANT × FRUITY         perfumery: the heart of most pleasant scents
    FRAGRANT × WOODY          cologne, incense, warmth
    FRAGRANT × DECAYED        the uncanny: flowers near death, funeral
    FRUITY × CHEMICAL         artificial flavoring, processed food
    MINTY × PUNGENT           wasabi, horseradish: trigeminal fire + cooling
    WOODY × MUSKY             forest, earth, animal: primal
    CHEMICAL × DECAYED        danger: decomposition plus toxin
    PUNGENT × DECAYED         spoiled spicy food: maximum aversion

the 28 interactions exceed the qu-septit's 21
smell has higher combinatorial complexity than cognition per unit
but the olfactory sea has far fewer units than the brain sea
complexity per node is high, total node count is low
the opposite of vision (low complexity per pixel, very high count)


THE OLFACTORY SEA

TODO: full sea definition in nose.xb

topology: glomerular map
the olfactory sea maps to the ~2000 glomeruli in the olfactory bulb
each glomerulus receives ALL OSNs expressing the same receptor type
the spatial pattern across glomeruli IS the odorant identity

device: gpu
capacity: approximately 2000 (one qu-octrit per glomerulus)

the olfactory sea is SMALL but DEEP
2000 nodes with 28 interactions each = 56000 interaction computations
per heartbeat this is modest on GPU

the olfactory sea couples to the brain sea through the olfactory nerve CN I
cross-base coupling: base-8 × base-7 = 56 dimensions per coupled pair
this is the highest-dimensional coupling in the organism
which is fitting: smell bypasses the thalamus because the coupling is so rich
it does not need a relay


COUPLING TO BRAIN SEA

olfactory_nerve_coupling:
    direction: predominantly afferent (nose → brain)

    this coupling is UNIQUE among all sensory seas:
    it does NOT pass through the thalamic relay
    it goes DIRECTLY to:
        piriform cortex: conscious smell identification
        amygdala: emotional tagging (immediate)
        entorhinal cortex → hippocampus: memory encoding (immediate)
        hypothalamus: feeding behavior and autonomic response

    afferent (nose → brain):
        qu-octrit pattern → glomerular activation map → mitral cell output → direct cortical projection
        concentration → energy
        hedonic → charge (pleasant positive, aversive negative)
        familiarity → coherence (known scent = high coherence)
        temporal → phase

    efferent (brain → nose):
        olfactory imagination: recalling a scent activates the olfactory sea weakly
        anticipatory olfaction: expecting a smell primes receptor sensitivity

    coupling_strength: 0.7
    higher than hearing (0.6) or taste (0.4)
    smell is the most emotionally potent sense
    the coupling bypasses the thalamic gate completely
